["English (Lancashire): habitational name from Ribby in Lancashire, named with Old Scandanavian <i>hryggr</i> ‘ridge’ + <i>bȳ</i> ‘farmstead, village’. Compare   Rigsby  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rigsby","meanings":["English: habitational name from Rigsby (Lincolnshire), probably from the genitive form of Old Norse <i>hryggr</i> ‘ridge’ + <i>bȳ</i> ‘farmstead, village’."]}]},{"name":"Helena","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Helen  , used also in Germany, the Netherlands, Scandinavia, and Eastern Europe."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":11,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":20,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":31,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":33,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":47,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":49,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Helena Rigby was born in 1538, in Standish, Lancashire, England. She married Ralph Pierpoint in 1560, in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1590, in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1538–1590":"1538–1590","1536–1592":"1536–1592","1561–Female":"1561–Surnud","1562–Male":"1562–Surnud","1564–1650":"1564–1650","23 SEP 1561":"23. september 1561","1561":"1561","1560":"1560","1571":"1571","28 SEP 1562":"28. september 1562","1592":"1592","1590":"1590","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1536":"1536","1587":"1587","1564":"1564","1585":"1585","1650":"1650","1562":"1562","1538":"1538","1549":"1549","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England, UK":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Standish,Lancashire,England":"Standish, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1538–1590":"1538–1590","1536–1592":"1536–1592","1561–Female":"1561–Kuollut","1562–Male":"1562–Kuollut","1564–